          <td bgcolor="" valign="top"><!-- #BeginEditable "Body" --> 
            <table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">
  <tr>
    <td>
      <table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="2" bgcolor="#FFFFFF">
        <tr>
          <td>
            <table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="2">
              <tr> 
                <td class="chpurple"><font class="h1font"><table cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 border=0 width=100%><TR><td><font class="h1font">Articles</td><form method='post' action=''><td align='right' valign='bottom'><select name='select' onChange='go(this)'><option selected>More DeckTech Articles</option><option value='#'> </option><option value='/starwarsccg/articles/index.php3'>Star Wars: CCG</option><option value='/vs/articles/index.php'>Marvel VS</option><option value='/heroclix/articles/articles.php'>HeroClix</option><option value='/lotr/articles/articles.php'>Lord of the Rings</option><option value='/magic/articles/articles.php'>Video Games and Movies</option><option value='/wars/articles/articles.php'>Wizards Minis</option></select></td></form></tr></table></font></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr><td><table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="3"><tr><td><font class="bfont"><font class="h1font"> Checklist for New Decks<br></font><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Overall Rating:</b> </font><img src="/magination/gfx/star3.gif" width="21" height="22" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/magination/gfx/star3.gif" width="21" height="22" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/magination/gfx/star3.gif" width="21" height="22" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/magination/gfx/star3.gif" width="21" height="22" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/magination/gfx/star3.gif" width="21" height="22" border="0" align="absmiddle"><font size='1'>(5.00)</font><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Author:</b> <A HREF='http://www.decktech.net/magination/main/mpage.php?member=15004'>Zach "Esper" Davis</A></font><font class="afont"> <a href='http://www.decktech.net/magination/main/mpage.php?member=15004&sub=1'> (Subscribe to this member)</a><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Date Submitted:</b> September 28, 2003</font><p align='justify'><font class="bfont"> OK, so you&#39;ve made a new deck. You&#39;ve found a good combo, found some good Magi to support it, and fit it into forty cards. But, have you really covered all your bases (Because, you know, if they&#39;re not covered, then all your base are belong to us. ...Sorry, couldn&#39;t resist!)? Here&#39;s a quick list of things to think about when you make a new deck... a paraphrased list of staples, if you will. Some of them are pretty obvious, but some of tham are not so obvious. Just read on already.<br />
<br />
-Do you have ways of killing Relics? <br />
A good deck should have at least two or three cards that can either kill Relics, steal them, or render them ineffective. Something as simple as Relic Stalker can do, or you can use Crushing Surf, or Beam of Light, or Rayje&#39;s Belt, or whatever. You don&#39;t want to have to deal with too many nasty Relics, though, so be sure you can get rid of them if you need to.<br />
<br />
-Do you have ways of drawing cards?<br />
I find that most good decks have at least two different methods of drawing more than two cards per turn, encompassing four or five slots in your deck. This number cna be reduced if you have a Magi who loves to cardmonger, but it&#39;s a good idea to have two plans for drawing cards.<br />
<br />
-Do you have ways of gaining energy outside of your Energize step?<br />
This is one that many people overlook, and it&#39;s the reason that well-constructed Nar decks are some of the strongest out there. But, Nar denial decks are not the only reason for this. It&#39;s always a good thing to have more energy on your Magi. Energy is the whole point of the game, and your Magi is the only means you have of flinging it about. Channeler&#39;s Gloves, Nagsis&#39; Sigil, Alaban Gloves... you want a method of grabbing a little extra when you need it.<br />
<br />
-Do you have ways of finishing off the opposing Magi?<br />
Many good combos will annihilate opposing creatures, but leave the Magi very much alive. A method of removing energy from opposing Magi is a vital part of every deck. You can&#39;t expect them to leave themselves energy-less every turn... if you are confident that your attacks will finish them off, that&#39;s great, but having another method is always good.<br />
<br />
-Do you have an unblockable method of harming Creatures?<br />
How well will you be able to stand up to a pumped Pylofuf or massive Flutter Yup? What about a Baby Furok controlled by Zannah? Can you get past big creatures that aren&#39;t easy to hurt by conventional means? Direct-discard is the most obvious methos of doing this, but there are others as well. Rayje&#39;s Sword, Rayje&#39;s Cloak (sometimes), or something unblockable like Ainjer or Lava Flow are good.<br />
<br />
-Can you handle being deprived of your abilities?<br />
What do you do when your opponent lays a Rayje&#39;s Belt (especially with a Relic Mirror around), or plays a Sandswirl on the key component of your combo? What about if they have Sorreah for a Magi? Can you handle being deprived of your Powers and Effects, or can you get rid of the restrictions somehow?<br />
<br />
-What do you do if your costs go up?<br />
Can you handle it if your cards suddenly cost more to play? Hrada, freezing cards, various Shadow Geysers, Vertigo, etc... what happens if you suddenly have to pay more for everything you like to do? Can you cancel it? Can you get the energy from auxiliary sources? Can you simply deal without doing everything you usually do?<br />
<br />
-What if one of your cards is 100% disabled?<br />
What do you do when your favorite Spell is suddenly Entombed/Cleansed, or zapped with Eyes of Arderial? Alternately, what if you can&#39;t play Creatures as you like to due to those nasty control cards on the field? Can you handle that?<br />
<br />
-Can you recover from widespread disaster?<br />
If your opponent suddenly lays a Cataclysm or Ormagon, can you stop it somehow? If not, how much will it set you back? Can you recover faster than they can? What if they try to force you to a new Magi with Trug? Can you prevent that from happening, or cope with the changes?<br />
<br />
-Can you deal with Spells on the field? <br />
This one isn&#39;t as important as many of the others, but the ability to get rid of an annoying Corrupt, or Shadow Geyser, or Will of Orothe, or Crystal Vision, or Pure of Heart, or whatever, is a valuable one.<br />
<br />
-Do you have a backup?<br />
What if your opponent pops a Spirit of Rayje or something similar to defend against your main onslaught? Can you regroup your forces and do it again next turn, or play something else to rid them of that last bit of energy?<br />
<br />
-Can you defend your hand?<br />
What if your opponent suddenly tries to get rid of your hand? Can you stop them somehow, or get something back from it? Gilded Cage, Climbing Staff, Tomorrow&#39;s Jewel, Abraxin&#39;s Crown, Shell, and the like are all excellent cards to keep around.<br />
<br />
-How easily can your main plan be foiled?<br />
Will your huge creature of death fall to a single Shockwave? Can you regenerate your swarm after a Typhoon drowns them all? Will your plot to deprive your opponent of their Creatures be ruined by a Creatureless deck? If so, get some kind of Plan B!<br />
<br />
I realize that you can&#39;t possibly prepare for every single kind of deck out there. Your deck would be unplayably clunky, not to mention huge. However, this checklist can help you scope out some of the possible weaknesses of your new deck... When I go reviewing, I notice a lot of the same flaws over and over. Maybe this will prevent some of them from appearing so much. <br></font><BR><font class="bfont"> <A HREF='/magination/articles/articles.php?id=5023&view=1'>Read the Reviews</a><font class="bfont"> | <A HREF='/magination/articles/articles.php'>Back to List</A></font><p><font class="bfont"> <b>You must be a member to contribute to Decktech.</b>  <p>Please <a href='/magination/main/join.php'> become a registered member</a></font></td></tr></table></td>
        </tr>
      </table>
    </td>
